-- Ghana Opposition to Name Bawumia as Running Mate, Joy Reports
-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 2012-01-16T13:57:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-16/ghana-opposition-to-name-bawumia-as-running-mate-joy-reports.html
Nana Akufo-Addo, presidential
candidate for  Ghana ’s main opposition party, is expected to
choose former central bank Deputy Governor Mahamudu Bawumia as
his running mate for a December election, Joy FM reported,
citing people it didn’t identify.  Akufo-Addo told party executives he wants to retain
Bawumia, who was his vice-presidential candidate in his 2008 bid
for the presidency,  according to  the Accra-based radio station.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Moses Mozart Dzawu in Accra at 
 mdzawu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
